(43, 5, 32, 43, 1, 33, 33, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness in both passages. John 5:32 speaks of a true witness, while John 1:33 refers to the Spirit descending as a sign of Jesus'' identity, serving as a divine witness to his role.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 43, 5, 36, 37, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Jesus'' Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness in both passages. In John 5:32, the idea of another witness is expanded in John 5:36-37, where the works of Jesus and the Father''s testimony serve as greater witnesses to His authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 62, 5, 6, 9, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of witness regarding Jesus Christ. John 5:32 speaks of a true witness, while 1 John 5:6-9 elaborates on the various witnesses, including the Spirit, water, and blood, affirming the truth of Christ''s identity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 40, 17, 5, 5, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Beloved Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the emphasis on a true witness aligns with Matthew 17:5, where God affirms Jesus as His beloved Son, indicating His authority and truth.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 41, 1, 11, 11, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of Divine Approval', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the emphasis on a true witness aligns with Mark 1:11, where God''s voice affirms Jesus as His beloved Son.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 32, 42, 3, 22, 22, 'witness which he witnesseth of me', 'Witness of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine witness. In John 5:32, the ''witness'' refers to the validation of Jesus'' identity, while in Luke 3:22, the Holy Spirit''s descent and the voice from heaven affirm Jesus as God''s Son.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 6, 8, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights the role of John as a witness. Both passages emphasize that John was sent to bear witness to the truth and the Light.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 15, 27, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John bearing witness to the truth about Jesus. John 5:33 refers to John''s testimony, while John 1:15-27 elaborates on his role in declaring Jesus'' identity and significance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 33, 43, 1, 29, 34, 'bare witness unto the truth', 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'This connection highlights John''s role as a witness to Jesus, as stated in both passages. John 5:33 refers to John''s testimony about the truth, while John 1:29-34 details John''s declaration of Jesus as the Lamb of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
