(43, 5, 34, 42, 19, 41, 42, 'that ye might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation and Peace', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and the recognition of peace. In John 5:34, the emphasis is on the need for salvation, while in Luke 19:41-42, the lament over Jerusalem reflects a missed opportunity for peace and salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 43, 20, 31, 31, 'that ye might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through belief in Jesus. Both passages emphasize the purpose of their messages: to lead individuals to faith and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 34, 62, 5, 9, 9, 'that ye might be saved', 'Witness and Testimony Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony, contrasting human witness with divine witness. Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s testimony regarding salvation and His Son.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
